The paper deals with image classification using deep learning techniques, specifically ResNet architectures. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses modifications to the ResNet architecture to improve classification accuracy, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of spatially weighted pooling and localisation also suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
